## Background
You are working with the Apideck Unified Issue Tracking API connected to GitHub (service id `github`). Your job is to drive a full comment-modification workflow on a single ticket: create the ticket, append a sequence of comments, edit one of them in place, and remove another. The final state on the remote ticket must match the expected configuration.

## Requirements
- Create exactly one ticket inside the collection identified by the `APIDECK_ISSUE_TRACKING_COLLECTION_ID` environment variable.
- Add four comments, then edit one and delete one, so that three comments remain at the end with the expected bodies.
- Persist a small log file with the identifiers your script created so the workflow is auditable.

